Looking for a local baecation spot that won't cost you an arm and a leg? These five areas are all a four-hour drive from Johannesburg or less. They offer affordable accommodation, ranging from relatively cheap backpacker establishments to bed and breakfasts – and a range of activities costing from as little as R10 per person. 1. Clarens, Free State This picturesque small town in the foothills of the Maloti Mountains offers beautiful natural surroundings and is great for sightseeing, dining and shopping. Activities on offer include archery, hot-air ballooning, hiking, abseiling, mountain biking, quad biking... the list is endless. A post shared by Marco Salmans (@marcosalmans) on Jan 31, 2018 at 6:37am PST  A post shared by DeWet Cilliers (@dwc_95) on Jan 29, 2018 at 7:37am PST    A post shared by BS Photography (@photagraphor) on Jan 25, 2018 at 2:43am PST  A post shared by Mandi Blaschczok (@blaschczok) on Jan 24, 2018 at 5:21am PST  A post shared by Kobus Smit (@kobus_smit_) on Jan 23, 2018 at 1:03am PST    2. Graskop, Mpumalanga Considered the gateway to the Panorama Route, this little town is considered a great base to visit nearby God's Window, the beautiful Kadishi Tufa waterfall, the Bourke's Luck potholes -- there are many stunning highlights on this route. A post shared by Wanderlust Holiday Packages (@wanderlustholidaypackages) on Jan 29, 2018 at 1:46am PST  A post shared by Southey Travel (@southey_travel) on Jan 29, 2018 at 11:03am PST  A post shared by Hazel Anne Thomas (@hazeyt93) on Jan 28, 2018 at 10:24am PST  A post shared by Aigul Lotfullina или #АйгульТВ (@lotfullina.aigul) on Jan 31, 2018 at 9:13pm PST   3. Hartbeespoort Dam, North West If you're looking at an escape that isn't too far away from home, then Harties may be it. With a variety of couple-friendly activities like extreme jet-boat rides, ziplining, horse riding and hiking, you and yours will be spoilt for choice. A post shared by jacqui@jaxwax.co.za (@jaxnooch) on Jan 28, 2018 at 11:31a